# Project Agent Rules — PX Template

This project uses the Living Design 3.5 (LD 3.5) design system. All UI must be built with LD components and semantic design tokens. No exceptions.

---

## MANDATORY PRE-TASK PROTOCOL — Ask Before You Build

Before writing a single line of code for any design or UI request, ask the relevant questions below. Do not assume. Do not guess. Do not start implementing.

| Task type | Ask about |
|---|---|
| New page or layout | Breakpoints, tokens, states, data freshness |
| Carousel / scroll list | Shadow clipping, auto-advance, touch targets |
| Tabs / nav / buttons | Active state per page, navigation route + delay |
| Animation / transition | Feel (spring? ease? instant?), duration, timing |
| Data / content update | Dates relative to today? Real vs randomized names/addresses? |

Only after receiving answers should implementation begin.

---

## Deployment

Deploying is powered by Netlify or Vercel via MCP integrations. Use the appropriate MCP tools. Never ask the user to run terminal commands.

---

## File Organization

Break complex pages into smaller files under client/features/[feature]/. Even within a single page, extract sections into auxiliary components to keep things maintainable. Split early and often.

---

## Component Rules — NO EXCEPTIONS

### Search before creating

Before writing any component, search in this order:
1. client/components/ui/ — Living Design 3.5 components
2. design-system-docs/ — MDX specs for all available components
3. guidelines/components/ — Implementation guides

### Never use external UI libraries

NEVER install or import from any external UI library. Banned libraries include:
- shadcn/ui, @radix-ui/*, @headlessui/*, @mui/*, antd, chakra-ui
- lucide-react, react-icons, heroicons (for icons)

### Never modify LD components

Do NOT edit any file in client/components/ui/. If a variation is needed, create a new wrapper component that composes the original.

### Consolidate duplicates immediately

If you find multiple components that serve the same purpose, consolidate to ONE canonical component, update all references, and delete the duplicates.

---

## Design Token Rules — CRITICAL

Never use hard-coded colors, spacing, or typography. Always use var(--ld-semantic-*) tokens with a hex fallback.

### Key tokens

| Token | Usage |
|---|---|
| `--ld-semantic-color-action-fill-primary` | Primary action (Walmart blue) |
| `--ld-semantic-color-text` | Body text |
| `--ld-semantic-color-text-subtle` | Secondary text |
| `--ld-semantic-color-surface` | Card / panel surface |
| `--ld-semantic-color-separator` | Dividers and section separators |
| `--ld-semantic-color-link` | Default link color |
| `--ld-semantic-font-family-sans` | Everyday Sans UI |

---

## Page Layout Rules

Every page uses the standard shell:


<div className={styles.root}>
  <MastHead />
  <div className={styles.appRow}>
    <AppSidebar menuItems={...} />
    <main className={styles.main}>
      {page content}
    </main>
  </div>
</div>
```

- Never use max-width constraints on page content containers
- Standard responsive breakpoints: 1024px, 768px, 480px
- Padding scale: 32px → 24px → 16px → 12px

---

## Pre-task Checklist

Before completing any task, verify:
- No @radix-ui/* imports
- No hard-coded hex colors anywhere
- No hard-coded px spacing values
- No inline SVGs
- No external icon libraries
- No raw <button>, <a>, <table>, <input>, <select>, <textarea> elements
- No custom sidebar, tab, or dropdown implementations
- No max-width on page content containers
- All styles use var(--ld-semantic-*) tokens exclusively
- All link colors use var(--ld-semantic-color-link-*) tokens
- All icons from @/components/icons
- Responsive breakpoints implemented for any new layout
- Theme compliance check passed

